    public interface ComputingMap<K,V>
extends ReadOnlyMap<K,V>
    Conceptually, this map behaves much like an ordinary map other than the semantics of putting a key value pair into the map. A ComputingMap is associated with a particular computation - which effectively is equivalent to a function from type K to type V. This means that we may simply add a key to the map and have the associated value be calculated and added automatically. This interface may form the basis of a caching system, for example.
